snippet.title: Prince Indah - Rapudo (Official Video) sms SKIZA 9846027 to 811
snippet.description:
Timeless Anthems: Prince Indah’s Sixth Studio Masterpiece

In the heart of timeless elegance, Timeless Anthems—the sixth album from Kenyan Ohangla icon Prince Indah emerges as a symphony of enduring rhythms and heartfelt storytelling. Adorned with an hourglass motif symbolizing eternity and flanked by grand bookshelves evoking wisdom’s vast library, the album’s artwork captures Prince Indah in regal crimson velvet, exuding poise and passion. 
This collection weaves traditional Luo melodies with modern pulses, crafted to resonate across generations, produced under the Malaika Music banner for a sound that’s both nostalgic and boundary-breaking.
Spanning 16 tracks, Timeless Anthems invites listeners into a world of love, reflection, and cultural pride. Standouts include the soulful opener "Ngima Dhano," the vibrant "Atieno Nyar Chula" paired with "Mama Love" the introspective "Pedeshe (Ajawa Marwa)," and the uplifting "Believe Me." 
Deeper cuts like "Rapudo,"  "Berna" (Above & Beyond), "Jofitina," "Mirima," "Jaherana ft Zegge Delongeur," "Nyasuba," "Jambaka," and the tender closer "Nyi Luo" and "I Love You" deliver anthemic hooks that linger long after the final note.
Set for its grand launch on November 8, 2025, this album is more than music—it’s a celebration of heritage reimagined for the future. Let Prince Indah’s voice carry you into infinity.

Artist: Prince Indah
Title: Timeless Anthems
Stream: https://tr.ee/Timeless_Anthems-Album_...
©EMC 2025

snippet.title: DUFLA DILIGON FT. FATHERMOH - ZOZA (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Kenyan dancehall star Dufla Diligon officially drops his highly anticipated new single “ZOZA” featuring the electrifying Fathermoh—now available on all digital streaming platforms starting Friday, December 3, 2025.

“ZOZA”, a Swahili slang term meaning “nice” or “good vibes,” captures the track’s upbeat, infectious, feel-good energy. Blending Dufla’s signature dancehall style with Fathermoh’s unique lyrical flair, the duo delivers a club anthem crafted to light up playlists, dance floors, and social trends across Kenya and beyond.

The audio was produced by Wakawaka, known for his dynamic modern sound, with guitars by Kenty, and mixed by Wakawaka & Igamba Mbiu. Final mastering was handled by Henrick Sam, giving the track a polished, international finish.

Completing the release is a visually captivating music video directed and edited by KG Brian, bringing a cinematic edge to the song’s high-energy vibe.

Following the success of “Donjo Maber” and “Rumours” (both featuring Iyanii), “ZOZA” marks another major milestone in Dufla Diligon’s evolving musical journey.

Thank you for the continued support—feel free to share widely and add “ZOZA” to your playlists.

In a new four-part documentary by Emmy and Grammy Award–winning executive producer Curtis “50 Cent” Jackson and Emmy Award-winning director Alexandria Stapleton, Sean Combs: The Reckoning is a staggering examination of the media mogul, music legend, and convicted offender. Through explosive, never-before-seen materials, including exclusive interviews with those formerly in his orbit, this documentary tells the story of a powerful, enterprising man and the gilded empire he built — and the underworld that lay just beneath its surface.
